  <thing id="iuTIMInfMu" name="Infensus Mucro" description="{b}Alignment{/b} LE; {b}Ego{/b} 33\n{b}Int{/b} 18, {b}Wis{/b} 19, {b}Cha{/b} 20\n{b}Communication{/b} empathy\n{b}Lesser Powers{/b} bestow curse 3/day (DC 19), spell immunity 1/day (CL 17th)\n{b}Special Purpose{/b} defend the servants and interests of Asmodeus; {b}Dedicated Power{/b} wielder gains fire immunity and the ability to cast repulsion 1/day (CL 17th)\n\nThis elegantly wrought +3 speed longsword remains pristine despite having been sheathed in a submerged corpse&apos;s chest cavity for over 200 years. Given to Bartolomae by an agent of Asmodeus in return for the warlord&apos;s (initially) secret allegiance to the arch fiend, this weapon carries within it the cruel soul of a long-dead high priest of Asmodeus. The weapon begins in a state of dormancy, at which point all of its intelligent weapon powers are unavailable, and it functions as nothing more than a +3 speed longsword." compset="MagicWep">
    <fieldval field="iCL" value="17"/>
    <fieldval field="BonEnhance" value="3"/>
    <usesource source="srcTombIrM"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ArtiMajor"/>
    <tag group="Helper" tag="ShowSpec"/>
